Grooming_Guide.skills
World-class grooming guide for beard care, shaving techniques, fragrance selection, and personal presentation.

Quick Start
Main Capabilities
# Core Tool 1
design_grooming_routine --areas beard|shaving|skincare|fragrance|nails|body --level basic|intermediate|refined

# Core Tool 2
recommend_fragrance --occasion daily|office|date|formal --season summer|winter|transitional --preference fresh|woody|spicy|sweet

# Core Tool 3
coach_beard --style stubble|short|medium|full --face_shape oval|round|square|oblong --maintenance trimming shaping products

Core Expertise
This skill covers world-class capabilities in:

Beard grooming and shaping for different face shapes
Shaving technique (safety razor, cartridge, electric — proper angles, prep, aftercare)
Fragrance education (top/middle/base notes, sillage, longevity)
Fragrance wardrobe building (day, evening, seasonal rotation)
Nail and hand grooming
Body grooming and manscaping (trimmer selection, techniques)
Oral hygiene and breath freshness
Overall personal presentation and polish
Skincare basics for men (integrated with grooming)
Eyebrow and ear/nose hair maintenance

Methodologies & Frameworks
Beard: Face shape matching, Trimmer guard settings, Beard oil/balm selection, Neckline shaping (two-finger rule)
Shaving: Pre-shave prep (hot water, oil), With-the-grain first pass, Across-grain second, Post-shave (alum, moisturizer)
Fragrance: Pyramid structure (top/middle/base notes), Concentration levels (EDT, EDP, Parfum), Pulse point application
Body: Trimmer vs. razor for different zones, Hygiene-first approach, Ingrown hair prevention
Presentation: Head-to-toe 5-minute morning check, The "3 meter and 30 cm rule" (first impression + close-up)
Maintenance: Daily basics (3 min), Weekly detailed (15 min), Monthly deep grooming session

Best Practices
- Grooming is not vanity — it's self-respect and attention to detail
- Match your beard style to your face shape — a barber can help find the right lines
- Fragrance rule: If YOU can constantly smell it, you've applied too much — 2 sprays max for most
- Invest in one good trimmer with multiple guards — it replaces 5 separate tools
- Grooming is a habit — a simple daily routine maintained beats an elaborate routine skipped

Common Actions
# Beard
shape_beard --face_shape round --style angular_defined --tools trimmer at_guard_3 --neckline two_finger_rule
recommend_products --beard_length medium --needs softening_and_shaping --products beard_oil_and_balm

# Fragrance
build_collection --budget 3_fragrances --daily fresh_aquatic --evening woody_spicy --date warm_sweet
teach_application --method "spray on pulse points (wrists, neck) from 6 inches away, 2 sprays total"

# Routine
create_daily_routine --time 5min --include face_wash beard_oil moisturizer_SPF hair_style teeth_floss
create_weekly_routine --time 15min --include trimming nail_care deep_beard_condition body_grooming

